1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:02,313
<i>Previously on</i> The O. C:

2
00:00:02,480 --> 00:00:05,392
- Why wouldn't she date him?
- He's using her.

3
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,875
- When I'm not around you, I miss you.
- You do?

4
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:09,519
That was <i>Save the Last Dance?</i>

5
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:12,672
That dance number at the end
was so inspiring.

6
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:15,400
Me and you,
we got unfinished business.

7
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:17,152
- Where's Kaitlin?
- You're in love.

8
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:18,673
Just be careful of that girl.

9
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:20,990
I love you.
And I think you love me too.

10
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,229
About Johnny?

11
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,755
- I'm with you.
- That's not the whole story, is it?

12
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:27,480
- Just come down, Johnny, please?
- Just be careful.

13
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:29,553
Johnny!

14
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:41,712
Well, you know what they say,
no news is good news.

15
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:44,394
I'm not sure that's true
about severe head injuries.

16
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:47,597
- We should've stayed at the hospital.
- Nothing we could do there.

17
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:50,320
The doctors told us to go home,
sleep, eat.

18
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:53,438
Yeah, except I can't sleep,
and I'm definitely not hungry.

19
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:56,190
- Hungry?
- Come on. Everyone needs to eat.

20
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:58,237
Johnny's gonna need you
when he wakes up.

21
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,719
- lf he wakes up.
- Marissa.

22
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:02,075
- You were there.
- Yeah, I was.

23
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:05,555
You guys, he's probably
gonna be fine.

24
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:08,553
Trey was unconscious for, like, months,
and he was fine.

25
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:09,709
And he was shot.

26
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:11,711
We waited around like this
once before...

27
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,110
...after a certain OD in TJ.

28
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:18,955
I'm gonna go check on Kaitlin
in the pool house.

29
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:25,200
- How you doing, Ryan?
- She's right.

30
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:27,954
I mean, the way the doctors
were talking, you could tell.

31
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:31,157
- They didn't wanna get our hopes up.
- Well, doctors are idiots.

32
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:34,392
- You tell that to your dad?
- It's their job to be negative.

33
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:39,156
It's called managing expectations.
That's why it's our job to be positive.

34
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,311
- Johnny's mom.
- You think you ought to...?

35
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:47,517
- I don't know.
- Do you want me to?

36
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,592
No, no. It's all right.

37
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:56,195
Mrs. Harper. Hey, it's Ryan.

38
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,479
What happened?

39
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,713
Hey.

40
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:27,353
- Thanks for coming by.
- No, I'm glad you called.

41
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:40,713
- Where's Gwen?
- I finally got her to lie down.

42
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,839
She started talking about the funeral
and just lost it.

43
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,197
- Well, what does she wanna do?
- Who knows.

44
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:50,636
She said no priest, no body,
nothing depressing.

45
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:53,235
It's a funeral.
Isn't it supposed to be depressing?

46
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,870
Well, I mean, we could do something
during the day.

47
00:03:57,040 --> 00:04:00,237
You know, maybe by the water.
No one allowed to wear black.

48
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,038
Or shoes.

49
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:06,192
Sounds like what he'd wanna do.

50
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:11,550
- I gotta take this to Mrs. H.
- Hey, I'll do it.

51
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,439
Thanks.

52
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,238
It doesn't seem real, man.

53
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,868
Listen, man, you can't blame yourself.
You tried.

54
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:22,318
- Yeah, and I failed.
- Well, don't beat yourself up.

55
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:25,074
Ryan Atwood versus himself
is a very ugly cage match.

56
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:27,629
I'm gonna shower,
try and get some sleep.

57
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:32,149
So I guess you won't worry about Johnny
coming between you and Marissa.

58
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:37,110
Because...
Sudoku? Fun to say, fun to do.

59
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:39,277
Too soon? Okay.

60
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,908
Too soon.

61
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:46,195
It just feels wrong. The kids
are going through this awful thing...

62
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:49,079
...and we're planning
a Valentine's Day dance.

63
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:52,232
All the more reason for them
to focus on something good.

64
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:56,518
I mean, it's not like we can cancel
this dance now if we wanted to.

65
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:59,832
Although, the thought
had crossed my mind.

66
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,068
- He hasn't asked you?
- Who? Dr. Neil Roberts?

67
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:05,231
Why, no, he hasn't.

68
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,470
- Think he has plans with someone else?
- No.

69
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,471
- That I'm not valentine material?
- Julie.

70
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:12,950
That I'm just a fun hang, not worthy
of chocolates and nice underwear?

71
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:15,111
Sandy's no fan
of Valentine's Day either.

72
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,754
We should just concentrate
on hosting a great event...

73
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:20,150
...and worry about
our love lives when it's over.

74
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:24,677
Or I could invent a fake reason to go
to his house and fish for information.

75
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,229
Julie, the last time you went
on a stealth mission...

76
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,675
...you toppled a dessert tray.

77
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,712
Yeah, but it got his attention.

78
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:34,997
- There you go.
- Thank you.

79
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,556
Hi. Are you a friend of Johnny's?

80
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:46,550
- I'm his cousin, Sadie.
- Hi. I'm glad you're here.

81
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,029
My mom thought it would
be a good idea if I came...

82
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,952
...and stayed with my aunt
for a while.

83
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,792
How's she doing?

84
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:55,349
Not so good, you know,
but finally sleeping.

85
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,511
You look like you could use
a few hours.

86
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,989
Oh, I'm okay.

87
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,912
- Yeah?
- Yeah. I should probably go.

88
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,991
I just got a lot of stuff to do.

89
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:08,631
- Hey, are you Marissa?
- Yeah.

90
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:11,155
Well, I wish it was
under better circumstances...

91
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,709
...but it's nice to finally meet you.

92
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,589
You too.

93
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,910
- Justin. What are you doing here?
- Winter break is almost over.

94
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:38,196
I thought you might want
a ride back to school.

95
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:41,272
- Should've saved your gas money.
- It's a hybrid.

96
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:44,477
Gets pretty good mileage,
so gas isn't an issue.

97
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,915
Last time you came to town
you wanted me arrested.

98
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:49,435
That was my brother.
And I was thinking...

99
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:53,388
I was hoping that we could talk.
About our relationship.

100
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,234
Our relationship?

101
00:06:57,200 --> 00:07:00,192
- Today's not a good day.
- Is there another day that'll be better?

102
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:04,353
- I want you to leave, right now.
- Kaitlin, are you okay?

103
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:10,276
I'll see you then. Thanks.

104
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,349
- Hey, boss.
- Hey.

105
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:15,239
- You wanted to see me?
- Got off the phone with Dr. Griffin.

106
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:19,188
The board has vetted the Brea proposal.
They're ready to put a hole in the ground.

107
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,396
But I'm gonna to meet with him
one more time.

108
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:25,473
Do you think you could call Maya?
I mean, with a few caveats.

109
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:28,632
- Name them.
- Don't lie. Don't lead her on.

110
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,153
That's not a problem.

111
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:33,232
The reason I went out with her
is, actually, I really like her.

112
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,152
Oh, boy likes girl.

113
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:39,838
Girl has access to influential father
boy's boss needs to close a deal.

114
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:43,470
Has all the makings of a great romance.
I'm glad you like her.

115
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:46,438
Well, I'll give her a call. Let you know.

116
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,511
- Hey, Marissa.
- Hi.

117
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,032
Marissa.

118
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:57,315
- How are you holding up?
- I'm okay.

119
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,549
I was wondering...

120
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,917
...there's all these forms
from the hospital and, well...

121
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:04,275
...Johnny's mom can't really
deal right now.

122
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,873
It doesn't need a lawyer...

123
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,349
You know, I actually know
just the guy for the job.

124
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:11,717
- I practically majored in paperwork.
- Are you sure you don't mind?

125
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:15,589
When it comes to mind-numbing
bureaucratic busywork, Matt is an ace.

126
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:19,833
- And here I thought you never noticed.
- All right, well, I should get home.

127
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,274
You know, shower.

128
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:23,908
I've been in these clothes since
you don't wanna know.

129
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,629
- I think you're doing great, kiddo.
- Thanks.

130
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:34,154
- Oh, hey.
- Hey, what are you doing?

131
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:36,629
Nothing.

132
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:40,914
Well, if it's nothing,
then you won't mind me looking, right?

133
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:44,072
- That's not porn.
- It's a list of my yakuza DVDs...

134
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:47,676
...sorted alphabetically by title
and also by director.

135
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,956
Making my inventories is
one of those things...

136
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,111
...like masturbating
or flossing my teeth...

137
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:55,477
...where even though you know I do it,
I'd rather you not witness it.

138
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:58,029
Cohen, I found something
in your drawer.

139
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:04,719
- You're not mad?
- Oh, no. I'm mad.

140
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:08,236
I'm livid. Not about the pot, because,
I mean, whatever, it's pot, right?

141
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,789
And while Marissa and I
were hotboxing Luke's car...

142
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:14,475
...you were at home making a manger
for Captain Oats out of Lincoln Logs.

143
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,631
You were a late bloomer, I get that.

144
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,519
But, Cohen, you lied to me for, like,
the gazillionth time.

145
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:23,309
- About something important.
- Summer, I don't know what I can do...

146
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:27,029
...except say I'm not gonna lie again
and then not lie.

147
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,634
- You just have to trust me.
- Yeah, well, I don't.

148
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,189
So you better think of something else.

149
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:41,031
- What happened to the Crock-Pot?
- It broke.

150
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:45,278
- Hi. Hey.
- Hi.

151
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,829
- Let me give you guys some privacy.
- It's all right.

152
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,276
- You don't have to leave.
- I've tried talking to her.

153
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:54,079
Well, give her some time.
How you doing?

154
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,037
You know...

155
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,879
Hi, Mrs. Harper.

156
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,795
Sorry, hi.

157
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:08,234
Yeah, I guess. Sure.

158
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,954
- Hi.
- Hey.

159
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:23,637
- Thanks for meeting me.
- Sure. No problem.

160
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:28,634
- So you visiting?
- Yeah. From Ashland, Oregon.

161
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:32,554
- You taking some time off school, or...?
- No, actually, I just graduated.

162
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:35,598
I started my own little
jewelry-making business.

163
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:40,231
So I've just been traveling,
trying to get stores to carry my stuff.

164
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:45,389
You know, I really need to be
with my boyfriend right now.

165
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:48,154
- Your boyfriend?
- Yeah. Ryan.

166
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:51,399
He was with me,
with Johnny, when it happened.

167
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:56,156
Oh, yeah, my aunt mentioned that there
was another kid there, I just thought...

168
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:59,671
This is really awkward. I thought
that Johnny was your boyfriend.

169
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,956
Why would you think that?

170
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,429
Because last week he called me,
and he asked me...

171
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:07,512
...if I would make something for you
for Valentine's Day.

172
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,113
Here, I brought it with me.

173
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:14,109
That there is your birth stone,
and that's his.

174
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,714
And in the middle there's an angel.

175
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,318
- An angel?
- Yeah.

176
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,436
He was afraid you'd think
it was cheesy...

177
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,194
...but he said that's what
you were to him.

178
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,790
Johnny and I were pretty close
growing up.

179
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:22,394
A couple of years ago,
I spent a summer in Newport...

180
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:25,279
...and I have to say, it was
the best summer of my life.

181
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:28,477
Johnny had this pair
of Power Ranger pajamas...

182
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,358
...he absolutely refused to take off.

183
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:33,871
I mean, he would literally wake up
in the morning...

184
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:36,031
...put his clothes on top
of his pajamas...

185
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:39,033
...and go about his day
wearing his two layers of clothing.

186
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,838
Ryan, there's Kaitlin.

187
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:07,437
- I should probably...
- No, it's all right. Let me.

188
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:15,231
- Hey, what are you doing up here alone?
- Well, what am I supposed to do?

189
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,233
Just go down there
and introduce myself?

190
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:21,790
"Hey, I'm Kaitlin,
the girl who killed him."

191
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:24,633
You didn't make him climb that rock,
didn't make him fall.

192
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:27,838
That's right. That was you.

193
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:32,396
You know what? I'm not gonna
do this with you.

194
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:35,677
- Everybody's upset. Come on.
- No, you know what, Ryan?

195
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,671
You can't fix this.

196
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:40,912
So just save the speeches
for my sister, all right?

197
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:46,349
All right, here you go. This is your
fourth-quarter bonus, by the way.

198
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:48,476
And next time, I pick the sport.

199
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:51,029
Hey, did you ever get
in touch with Maya?

200
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,673
Yeah. But I kind of wish I didn't.

201
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:58,868
When I didn't call her back, she took
that as a sign of my lack of interest.

202
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,429
She's a smart girl,
and now she's an angry one too.

203
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,875
It's not a typo.
I need 10,000 cinnamon hearts.

204
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:06,474
And please don't make them stale.
Thanks.

205
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,153
Hey, honey, are the kids home?

206
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,515
No. They're going
to The Bait Shop for the wake.

207
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,875
- Hey, Matt, how's it going?
- Woman troubles.

208
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:16,715
- Oh, well, maybe I can play cupid.
- That's a great idea.

209
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,872
Really, Sandy? And what is it
that you say about Valentine's Day?

210
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:23,191
That it's vacuous, a commercially-driven,
hollow shell of a holiday?

211
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:26,079
Sometimes we need a vacuous,
commercially-driven diversion.

212
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,629
- This would be one of those times.
- What's her name?

213
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,995
- I'll have a ticket delivered.
- Maya Griffin.

214
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:34,596
Whose father's the head
of the physician's board?

215
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:37,030
- I don't know.
- lf anybody can do it, you can.

216
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,794
She doesn't need my help
getting a date. It won't work.

217
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,030
You know what, Kirsten,
don't worry about it.

218
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,919
I'm sure that we can come up
with something else.

219
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:50,473
I'll get Maya to the party
if you try and embrace the holiday.

220
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:55,475
No whining, no snarky comments.
Candies, candles, lingerie. Nice lingerie.

221
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:59,235
Nothing red, see-through,
or remotely edible.

222
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,197
Not even a little see-through?

223
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,638
Death and Valentine's Day,
there's an unbeatable combination.

224
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,837
This is the first one where Marissa and I
are actually together.

225
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,037
- Should be all-time.
- Pressure's on for me to deliver.

226
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:19,953
- Summer found my stash.
- You don't have any visible bruises.

227
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:22,873
- She go for the kidneys?
- I wish.

228
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,474
You and Atwood make V-Day plans?

229
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,551
