But is it more than that? I mean...

467
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:47,159
...when's the last time we actually
hung out together, alone?

468
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:49,713
What, you mean without Johnny?

469
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:56,278
You're glad he's gone, aren't you?

470
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,754
No, I'm not even gonna answer that.

471
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:43,748
So did Summer
give you back the bag?

472
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:47,117
The conversation kind of went
in a different direction after that.

473
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:49,999
- Hey. No Marissa?
- Yeah. No Summer either?

474
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,713
She's over there with her date.

475
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:55,436
Valentine's Day,
it's too much pressure.

476
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,471
There's Matt. Has his date shown up?

477
00:30:57,640 --> 00:30:59,551
Cool. Another dude.
I gotta do something.

478
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:22,800
You gonna try to act
like this is a strange coincidence?

479
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:25,314
Not anymore.

480
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:31,438
- Can I buy you a drink?
- I don't know, can you?

481
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:34,594
Still got that fake ID?

482
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:45,079
Happy Valentine's Day, sir.

483
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:48,511
I was wondering if I could maybe
borrow your daughter for a moment.

484
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,278
I'm right here. What do you want?

485
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:56,155
I wrote you something.

486
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:59,033
- A cocktail napkin?
- It's a confession. Read it.

487
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:02,751
"To whom it may concern:

488
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:06,151
My name is Seth Cohen,
and I have problem with flying."

489
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:08,470
It says "lying." Pen shook.

490
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:12,754
"I have lied about many things
over the years.

491
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:16,913
The most recent and troubling lies include
but are not limited to the following:"

492
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:19,389
There's a complete list
on the back of the napkin.

493
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:21,790
All my sins. Very detailed.

494
00:32:21,960 --> 00:32:23,632
- Cohen, I know all of this.
- I know.

495
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:26,439
But if I ever screw up again,
you give that to my parents.

496
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:31,391
That's pretty smart.

497
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:33,472
You may have just rocked my world.

498
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:37,075
A half-court shot at the buzzer.

499
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:39,356
Is that a sports metaphor?
I don't follow.

500
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:42,110
I'm wearing the thong.

501
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:45,635
Yeah, that's my mom's.

502
00:32:57,440 --> 00:33:00,512
- What are you doing?
- Getting wasted.

503
00:33:03,760 --> 00:33:04,875
You and me, Marissa.

504
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:10,031
We're the only people who understand
what we're going through.

505
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,919
You might be right about that.

506
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:17,032
This emotional connection
might be a really good platform...

507
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,519
...for a more physical one.

508
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:22,229
I'm not gonna
make out with you, Chili.

509
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:24,753
It's not Chili anymore.

510
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:26,592
I'm going back to Dennis.

511
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:28,432
Johnny never liked that nickname.

512
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,553
Care for some oysters, ma'am?

513
00:33:42,720 --> 00:33:44,676
Oh, no. I don't do oysters.

514
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:46,831
If I'm gonna swallow something
disgusting...

515
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:49,070
...there better be something
in it for me.

516
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:52,676
- Hey, Mom.
- Oh, hey, baby. How are you?

517
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:55,354
I was thinking about leaving.

518
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:57,317
Oh, then I'll see you
back at the house.

519
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:59,789
No, I mean leaving Newport.

520
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:02,670
Going back to school. Tonight.

521
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:05,229
Justin, he offered to give me a ride.

522
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:08,234
Hello. Julie Cooper-Nichol,
Kaitlin's mother.

523
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:11,676
Very nice to meet you.
You have a lovely daughter.

524
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:15,674
I'll drive under the speed limit,
make sure she buckles her seatbelt.

525
00:34:15,840 --> 00:34:18,149
Stop for coffee several times.

526
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:22,595
Thank you, Justin. I appreciate that.

527
00:34:24,960 --> 00:34:26,757
Well, I'll see you at parents' weekend.

528
00:34:26,920 --> 00:34:28,876
Promise me you're definitely
coming back.

529
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:31,474
I promise.
You'll be seeing a lot more of me.

530
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:36,598
Kaitlin, I'm so sorry if this trip
wasn't everything you hoped for.

531
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:39,399
I'm a Cooper, Mom. I'll survive.

532
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:46,038
Okay, bye.

533
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:57,000
- Hey.
- Hello there.

534
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:59,515
- You look radiant tonight.
- Thank you.

535
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:00,715
Hoping we could talk.

536
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:03,348
- You don't have to explain.
- No, I think I do.

537
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:06,671
All this back and forth,
coming together, pulling away again...

538
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:09,559
...I think it's happening for a reason.

539
00:35:09,720 --> 00:35:11,039
We don't belong together.

540
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:13,430
We both have very complex lives...

541
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:16,068
...which will make this
very complicated.

542
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:19,152
Right. I mean, who's looking
to make life any more complicated?

543
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:23,119
Did you say "will"?

544
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,669
I'm sorry it's taken me
this long to ask you this...

545
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:29,797
...but I lost my nerve
and I wasn't trusting my instincts.

546
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:32,232
But, Julie...

547
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,399
...would you be my Valentine?

548
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:42,875
All alone tonight?

549
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:45,629
That's to be expected
under the circumstances.

550
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:48,394
Marissa and I have been fighting a lot.

551
00:35:48,560 --> 00:35:51,518
Mainly about whether Johnny
was just a friend.

552
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:54,274
- Or if it was more than that.
- She says it wasn't.

553
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,317
I don't think she's lying to me...

554
00:35:56,720 --> 00:35:58,995
...but she might be lying to herself.

555
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:02,757
And now that he's gone,
I don't know how we move forward.

556
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,794
- Or if.
- Well, the night's not over.

557
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:08,679
Maybe there's a pit stop
you can make on the way home.

558
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:12,310
Yeah, actually, there is.

559
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:19,832
How's Ryan?

560
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:24,039
Oh, he has a lot on his mind, as usual.

561
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:28,073
Matt and Maya
seem to be getting along.

562
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:30,800
- Think they're talking about business?
- Yeah.

563
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:35,078
I think right now he's saying
how our design offers more space...

564
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:38,869
...for emergency care
and outpatient services.

565
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:42,750
I think she's more concerned
about wheelchair access in the lobby.

566
00:36:42,920 --> 00:36:45,718
Oh, she's a good soul.

567
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:01,116
- Are you leaving?
- Yeah.

568
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:03,748
Don't cry or anything.

569
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:06,992
Look, I know this wasn't
the best vacation you've ever had...

570
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:11,757
...but I really am sorry for everything.

571
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:14,593
Don't be. Just figure it all out.

572
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,709
- Figure what out?
- What you really felt for Johnny.

573
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:23,196
What does it matter now?

574
00:37:25,520 --> 00:37:28,318
Keep telling yourself whatever you want,
but it does matter.

575
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,959
I'm really glad you came back.

576
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:42,711
I kind of sort of maybe
might believe you.

577
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:51,639
- Hi.
- Hi.

578
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:53,711
I was wondering if I could
give you a hand?

579
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:56,394
No, no, I got it. Thank you.

580
00:37:57,320 --> 00:37:59,754
- Okay, I'll just...
- I mean, really?

581
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:02,992
Yeah, yeah.
Figured you could use the help.

582
00:38:05,080 --> 00:38:06,911
I can make the conversation
more awkward.

583
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:09,150
Well, in that case, please.

584
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:21,189
Hey, Kait, I think
there's something in your eye.

585
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:23,191
It couldn't be. Is that a tear?

586
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:25,191
Shut up.

587
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:31,070
You know, as weird as it may sound...

588
00:38:32,040 --> 00:38:34,110
...I think I'm actually
gonna miss this place.

589
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,558
What are you thinking?

590
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:48,713
If I could've done or said anything...

591
00:39:50,720 --> 00:39:52,790
...that would've saved him.

592
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:58,229
Well, I think it's a hard thing
to accept...

593
00:39:58,400 --> 00:40:00,436
...that life's completely
out of our control.

594
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,833
But you were there for him.

595
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:06,719
End of the day, that's all
we can really do for each other.

596
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:08,991
Just be there.

597
00:40:10,920 --> 00:40:12,831
And I'll be in the kitchen
if you need me.

598
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:34,189
Go away.

599
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:36,351
- I just wanna talk.
- There's nothing to say.

600
00:40:36,520 --> 00:40:38,795
You wouldn't have come
if you didn't wanna see me.

601
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:41,952
Got nothing to do with you.
Leave before I scream for the cops.

602
00:40:42,120 --> 00:40:43,917
We both know
you're not gonna do that.

603
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:48,075
What the hell is he doing here?

604
00:40:49,240 --> 00:40:51,071
Everything okay?

605
00:40:54,640 --> 00:40:56,551
It is now.

606
00:40:57,560 --> 00:40:59,039
You want tea?

607
